\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Position-swap control experiment.} Top row: layer-wise KL divergence for system- vs.\ user-token patching under each layout (Y-axes unified for direct comparison). Bottom row: total KL summed over layers. Causal influence concentrates at sequence-final positions regardless of content placement (Normal: user~118.3 vs.\ system~0.001; Swapped: user~105.8 vs.\ system~0.000), revealing a positional (autoregressive bottleneck) component. Both conditions show identical early-layer dominance (L0--L2), confirming attention-mediated persona propagation as the mechanistic driver.}}{14}{figure.caption.42}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:position_swap}{{6}{14}{\textbf {Position-swap control experiment.} Top row: layer-wise KL divergence for system- vs.\ user-token patching under each layout (Y-axes unified for direct comparison). Bottom row: total KL summed over layers. Causal influence concentrates at sequence-final positions regardless of content placement (Normal: user~118.3 vs.\ system~0.001; Swapped: user~105.8 vs.\ system~0.000), revealing a positional (autoregressive bottleneck) component. Both conditions show identical early-layer dominance (L0--L2), confirming attention-mediated persona propagation as the mechanistic driver}{figure.caption.42}{}}
